From Brian Casey Subject Re MAC DISKS IN WINDOWS In article Michael Panayiotakis writes In article Gilles KHOUZAM writes on is supposed to read and write Mac I've never tried it Good luck I just tried it but I can't say that it works 'cause it doesn't read disks it only reads If there a program that does read disks please let me Well you can't say that it don't The inability to read mac disks is not a SW Rather it's a HARDWARE limmitation on I have seen a post about a program able to read non Mac disks which comes with a watchamacalit ma memory's faling card which you just drop into a com port or Don't remember specifics peace Mickey On all drives both Mac and PC the disk spins at a constant On Mac disk drives the spin rate of the disk is varied so that the tracks pass under the head at a constant speed a slower rotation for the outer tracks and a faster rotation for the inner A PC needs special controller hardware to make this Brian Casey